instruction:
Sometimes you need a struct for one specific thing and do not need to reuse it. An anonymous struct has no type name — it is defined and used inline.

```
config := struct {
    Host string
    Port int
}{Host: "localhost", Port: 8080}
```

Run this. Notice there is no `type Config struct` declaration anywhere — the struct is defined right where it is used.

